11 Section 1. R.S. 37:21 is hereby amended and reenacted to read as follows:
12 §21. Limitations on disciplinary proceedings by professional or occupational boards
13 and commissions; recovery of attorney fees and costs
14 A.(1) Unless a special law is applicable, no proceeding of any kind may be
15 initiated by a professional or occupational board or commission as follows:
16 (a) If the nature of the complaint is based on negligence or gross negligence,
17 no proceeding may be initiated after two years from discovery by the complainant.
